- chr() function can be used to convert an ASCII ordinal number to a character
- ord() function does the opposite

- bytes.fromhex() function can be used to convert hex to bytes
- .hex() instance method can be called on byte strings to get the hex representation.
- b64encode() encode the string into the binary form.

PYCRYPTODOME
- bytes_to_long(): Convert a byte string to a long integer.
- long_to_bytes(): Convert a long integer to a byte string.


- zip(): function is used to combine two or more lists (or any other iterables) into a single iterable, where elements from corresponding positions are paired together